As of the 2010 census, there were 186 people living in the CDP: 87 male and 99 female. 35 were 19 years old or younger, 12 were ages 20–34, 33 were between the ages of 35 and 49, 57 were between 50 and 64, and the remaining 49 were aged 65 and above. The median age was 54.7 years.

The racial makeup of the CDP was 95.2% [[White Americans|White]], 0.5% [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 3.8 [[Race (United States Census)|Other]], and 0.5% [[Race (United States Census)|two or more races]].  5.4% of the population were [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race.

There were 80 households in the CDP, 58 family households (72.5%) and 22 non-family households (27.5%), with an average household size of 2.33. Of the family households, 48 were married couples living together, while there were 4 single fathers and 6 single mothers; the non-family households included 17 adults living alone: 5 male and 12 female.

The CDP contained 102 housing units, of which 80 were occupied and 22 were vacant.<ref name="GR2">{{Cite web |title=American FactFinder: Pinion Pines CDP, Arizona |url=https://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/1600000US0455983 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://archive.today/20200213103221/https://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/1600000US0455983 |archive-date=February 13, 2020 |access-date=January 30, 2017 |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]}}</ref>

As of July 2016, the average home value in Pinion Pines was $338,487. The average household income was $69,544, with a per capita income of $30,311.<ref name="AZL">{{Cite web |title=Pinion Pines CDP, Arizona – Basic Facts |url=http://arizona.hometownlocator.com/az/mohave/pinion-pines-cdp.cfm |access-date=January 30, 2017 |publisher=AZ Hometown Locator}}</ref>

